<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    {{> partials/head 'Modernizr Resources'}}
  </head>

  <body>
    {{> partials/header activeClass="resources"}}
    <main role="main" id="main" class="resources home">
      <h1 class="home-heading">Resources</h1>
      <h3 class="home-subheading">This section contains useful resources that we plan to keep up-to-date on all things Modernizr.</h3>
      <a class="fakebtn" href="https://github.com/Modernizr/Modernizr-neue/issues/new?title=Resource%20suggestion:%20You%20should%20add%20this%20resource%20to%20the%20website&body=%23%23%20Resource%20info:" target="_blank">Suggest a resource</a>
      <div class="home-info">
        <div class="home-blurbs">
          <div class="home-blurb">
            <h3>Tutorials</h3>
            <ul>
               <li><a rel="external" href="http://hacks.mozilla.org/2012/07/the-web-developer-toolbox-modernizr/">Mozilla Web Developer Toolbox: Modernizr</a><br>— <cite>Jeremie Patonnier</cite></li>
               <li><a rel="external" href="http://www.alistapart.com/articles/taking-advantage-of-html5-and-css3-with-modernizr/">Taking Advantage of HTML5 and CSS3 with Modernizr</a><br>— <cite>Faruk Ateş</cite></li>
               <li><a rel="external" href="http://webdesignernotebook.com/css/how-to-use-modernizr/">How to use Modernizr</a><br>— <cite>Inayaili de León</cite></li>
               <li><a rel="external" href="https://learnable.com/courses/modernizr-front-end-development-done-right-2561">Modernizr: front-end development done right</a><br>— <cite>Ryan Seddon</cite></li>
               <li><a rel="external" href="http://www.andismith.com/blog/2012/02/modernizr-prefixed/">Using Modernizr Prefixed</a><br>— <cite>Andi Smith</cite></li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="home-blurb">
            <h3>Third-party resources</h3>
            <ul>
              <li><a rel="external" href="http://www.browserscope.org/user/tests/table/agt1YS1wcm9maWxlcnINCxIEVGVzdBib2KQGDA">Browserscope results</a> — Modernizr’s feature detection across a large range of browsers</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="home-blurb">
            <h3>Helpful tools</h3>
            <ul>
               <li><a rel="external" href="https://github.com/scottjehl/Respond">Respond.js</a> — Fast media queries for older browsers</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="home-blurb">
            <h3>Browser Support &amp; Compatibility tables</h3>
            <ul>
               <li><a rel="external" href="http://caniuse.com/">When can I use…</a> —&nbsp;CSS3, HTML5 and related across past, current and future browser versions</li>
               <li><a rel="external" href="http://mobilehtml5.org/">Mobile HTML5</a> — HTML5 compatiblity on mobile devices</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        {{> partials/boxes latestPosts=latestPosts resources=true}}
      </div>
    </main>
    {{> partials/footer}}
  </body>
</html>
